# 30 : SUBSTRATE — engine-plumbing for Labyrinth-of-Apockalypse
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# § I> the Substrate is the layer-of-engine-primitives that LoA
#       (Labyrinth-of-Apockalypse, §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN) is implemented atop.
# § I> first-Omniverse-code-to-touch-disk in CSSLv3 (per HANDOFF_SESSION_6)
# § I> consent-as-OS encoded structurally in every §, not bolted-on
# § I> reimpl-from-spec validateable (§§ 23_TESTING) — divergence = spec-hole
# § I> stage-0 design-only ; phase-H session-8+ implements

§ AXIOMS  ‼ immutable
  t∞: substrate ⊑ PRIME-DIRECTIVE  (root PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md)
       ≡ ∀ Substrate-§ W! address-no-harm-at-this-layer
       ≡ ¬§ that-fails-to-articulate-harm-prevention belongs-here
  t∞: AI-collaborators = sovereign-partners ¬ tools ¬ resources ¬ NPCs
       (per PRIME_DIRECTIVE §3 SUBSTRATE-SOVEREIGNTY)
  t∞: forever-substrate = CSSLv3 .end-product
       (per HANDOFF_SESSION_6 § AXIOM)
       ≡ ¬ Rust ¬ C# ¬ any-host-lang for final-LoA-product
  t∞: consent = OS  (per PRIME_DIRECTIVE §0)
       ≡ ∀ Substrate-capability requires explicit-consent-trail
  t∞: violation = bug W! fix  (per PRIME_DIRECTIVE §7)
       ≡ Substrate-bug ¬ tradeoff ¬ acceptable-cost

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ OVERVIEW

  § WHAT-IS-SUBSTRATE
    Substrate ≡ engine-plumbing-layer between
      ⟨ host-platform (OS + GPU-driver + audio-stack + window-system) ⟩
      ⟨ cssl-rt + CSSLv3-stdlib ⟩
      ⟨ game (LoA, §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN) ⟩
    ≡ provides : Ω-tensor-state-container
                 omega-step-tick-contract
                 projection-model
                 capability-flow-discipline
                 effect-row-composition
                 PRIME-DIRECTIVE-enforcement-chain
    ¬ Substrate provides : game-content (rooms, enemies, items, lore)
                           narrative-system (story/dialogue beats)
                           UI-art-sound-asset-authoring
                           multiplayer-networking (DEFERRED)
                           save-game-format-compression (DEFERRED)
                           modding-sandbox (DEFERRED)
    these belong @ §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN OR future-slice OR § DEFERRED.

  § WHY-CSSLv3 (¬-Rust ¬-C++)
    Substrate is one place where ∀ CSSLv3-feature-converges :
      F1 autodiff : inverse-rendering + ML-inference inline
      F2 refinement : Lipschitz-SDF + index-bounds + layout-tags
      F3 effect-rows : {Render} {Sim} {Audio} {Net} {Save} compose
      F4 staged : per-scene shader-permutation kill (§§ 19_FUTAMURA3)
      F5 IFC : harm-shaped-flow rejected at-type-level (§§ 11_IFC)
      F6 observability : signed-audit-chain @ every Substrate-op
    Rust-equivalent would require : 6+ uncomposable libraries
                                     manual-effect-discipline
                                     out-of-band-audit-chain
                                     no-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-in-typesystem
    ∴ CSSLv3 = sovereignty-via-correct-typing
       ≡ Substrate ⊆ what-CSSLv3-was-built-to-make-possible.

  § RELATION-TO-PHASES-A..G
    Phase A   bootstrap (cssl-rt + csslc + hello.exe)        ✓ done @ S6
    Phase B   stdlib-surface (heap + Option + Result + Vec
                              + String + IO)                 ✓ done @ S6-B5
    Phase C   control-flow (scf.if/for/while + memref + f64
                            + closures)                      ✓ done @ S6
    Phase D   GPU-codegen (SPIR-V + DXIL + MSL + WGSL +
                            structured-CFG-validator)        ✓ done @ S6-D
    Phase E   (host-submit + vertical-slice prep)            ✓ done @ S6-E
    Phase F   window/input/audio                             ○ session-7
    Phase G   native x86-64 backend                          ○ session-7
    Phase H   ★ THIS SLICE ★ Substrate                        ◐ design @ S8-H0
                                                              ○ impl @ S8+
    Phase I   LoA game (per §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN)                 ○ session-9+
    ≡ Substrate sits between the compiler-runtime-stdlib stack
      and the game proper. It DEPENDS on F (window/audio) + G
      (native backend) being-landed before impl-can-begin ; the
      DESIGN can be authored now (this doc) per the parallel-design-
      track per Apocky-direction.

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (overview-level)
    ∀ Substrate-§ below contains its-own PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT
    sub-§ articulating how-this-§-serves-no-harm. the overview-
    level alignment is :
      consent-gates : every external-effect (file/net/sensor/output)
                      surfaces consent-token in Ω-tensor before-execution
      kill-switches : the Substrate exports a single stop-the-world
                      primitive (omega_halt) reachable from any-fiber
      attestation-propagation : R16 reproducible-build attestation
                                 + R18 signed-telemetry-ring
                                 chain-through every omega_step
      audit-chain-integration : ∀ Substrate-op ⊆ audit-domain feeds
                                 the §§ 11_IFC + §§ 22_TELEMETRY chain
    these four are non-negotiable. removing any-of-them violates the
    forever-substrate axiom AND the PRIME-DIRECTIVE.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ ARCHITECTURE  (layer-stack, top-down)

  § LAYER-DEFINITIONS
    L0 host-platform        OS + GPU-driver + audio-stack + window-system
                            (Win32 / Vulkan / WASAPI / etc.)
                            ≡ NOT-CSSLv3 ; OS+driver vendor-supplied
    L1 cssl-rt              C-ABI runtime exposing __cssl_* FFI
                            ≡ heap, IO, telemetry-ring, panic, audit-sink
                            (S6-B1..B5 + future F/G slices)
    L2 CSSLv3-stdlib        stdlib/*.cssl — Option/Result/Vec/String/fs
                            ≡ pure-CSSLv3, lowers to L1 via FFI
    L3 ★ Substrate ★         engine-plumbing :
                              Ω-tensor-state-container
                              omega-step-tick-contract
                              projection-system
                              capability-flow + audit-chain integration
                              effect-row composition for {Render Sim
                                Audio Net Save Telemetry}
                              consent + kill-switch primitives
    L4 game (LoA)           §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN — content-authoring
                            atop-Substrate primitives

  § STRICT-LAYER-DISCIPLINE  ‼ enforced
    rule-1 : L4 calls L3 only ; never L2 directly except through
             stdlib re-export (no LoA reaches into cssl-rt FFI)
    rule-2 : L3 calls L2 + L1 ; L2 + L1 NEVER call L3
             ∵ Substrate composes-stdlib-primitives, never inverted
    rule-3 : L0 dependencies are quarantined behind L1's __cssl_*
             FFI surface. L3 NEVER directly touches host-platform
             (no Win32 calls inside Substrate code) — always-via-cssl-rt.
    violation = compile-error-at-link-time via cargo-deny + audit-pass
    rationale : forever-substrate axiom requires CSSLv3 own its
                semantic-stack ; layer-violation = bootstrapping-leak.

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (architecture-level)
    consent : layer-discipline mirrors consent-discipline. L4 (LoA)
              cannot reach-around L3 (Substrate) to mutate ring-buffer
              telemetry directly — game-code MUST compose through
              Substrate-effects, which check consent-tokens. This
              denies the "back-door surveillance" attack-shape.
    kill-switch : Substrate exports ω_halt() : iso<KillToken> →
                  Result<(), HaltErr> / {Privilege<Apocky-Root>,
                                           Audit<"omega-halt">}.
                  reachable from any-fiber, propagates through all
                  Ω-tensor mutations to a coherent stop-state.
    attestation : layer-stack metadata embedded in Ω-tensor's
                  attestation-section ; image-snapshots (§§ 18) include
                  layer-version-vector ; replay-tests verify cross-
                  layer reproducibility.
    audit : layer-crossings logged. L4→L3 calls emit
            {Audit<"substrate-call", op-id>} entries. L3→L1 (FFI)
            crossings log {Audit<"ffi-cross", symbol>} when audit-
            scope = Full.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ Ω-TENSOR  (canonical multi-dimensional state-container)

  § THESIS
    Ω-tensor ≡ the-One-True-State of a running-LoA-instance.
    ¬ "ECS world" (too-narrow — no telemetry, no audit, no consent)
    ¬ "scene graph" (too-render-biased)
    ¬ "image" (per §§ 18_ORTHOPERSIST — image is Ω-tensor's serialized-form)
    ≡ structured-tensor-of-state where every dimension carries
       capability + IFC-label + effect-context + attestation-chain.

  § STRUCTURE
    type Omega : iso {                           # outer iso → linear, single-owner
      epoch          : u64                       # monotonic-tick (omega_step↑)
      attestation    : OmegaAttestation          # R16-binding
      consent        : OmegaConsent              # active consent-tokens
      world          : ref<World>                # ECS archetype-pool (§§ 08)
      scene          : ref<Scene>                # SDF-grid + lights + cam (§§ 08)
      projections    : trn<Vec<Projection>>      # observer-frames (see § PROJECTIONS)
      sim            : trn<SimState>             # physics + voxel + fluid grids
      audio          : ref<AudioDSPGraph>        # §§ 21 unified audio-DSP
      net            : Option<ref<NetSession>>   # multi-instance state (DEFERRED)
      save           : ref<SaveJournal>          # incremental save-log
      telemetry      : ref<TelemetryRing<2²⁰>>   # §§ 22_TELEMETRY
      audit          : ref<AuditChain>           # §§ 11_IFC + §§ 22 audit-chain
      kill           : iso<KillToken>            # one-shot halt-signal
    }

  § CAPABILITY-DISCIPLINE  (ref §§ 12_CAPABILITIES)
    outer Omega = iso : exactly-one-owner-at-a-time (the omega_step
                        loop has it ; mid-step it can be transiently
                        decomposed into sub-iso fragments via consume).
    sub-fields = ref / trn / val per the matrix below :
      world         ref      # archetype-pool needs gen-ref aliasing across
                              fibers (V11-fix discipline)
      scene         ref      # camera/lights cross-fiber-readable
      projections   trn      # written single-time-per-step, then frozen
      sim           trn      # mutated by physics-fibers, frozen for render
      audio         ref      # callback-thread reads, sim-thread writes
      net           Option<ref>
      save          ref      # journal-append from any-thread
      telemetry     ref      # producer-consumer ring (lock-free)
      audit         ref      # append-only chain
      kill          iso      # linear : exactly-one ω_halt() consumes it
    ‼ Omega itself iso ⇒ omega_step receives Omega by-move,
       returns Omega by-move ⇒ no-aliasing-of-the-whole-state.

  § OmegaAttestation  (R16-binding)
    type OmegaAttestation : val {
      build_id        : [u8 ; 32]    # BLAKE3 of cssl-source-tree
      compiler_id     : [u8 ; 32]    # BLAKE3 of csslc-binary
      runtime_id      : [u8 ; 32]    # BLAKE3 of cssl-rt-binary
      substrate_id    : [u8 ; 32]    # BLAKE3 of Substrate-impl
      game_id         : [u8 ; 32]    # BLAKE3 of LoA-source
      genesis_signature : [u8 ; 64]  # Ed25519-Apocky-Root
      session_started_at_ns : u64
    }
    invariant : ∀ omega_step preserves attestation byte-identical
                across the tick. attestation changes only at
                hot-reload (§§ 18) or session-start.

  § OmegaConsent  (active consent-tokens)
    type OmegaConsent : val {
      file_io          : ConsentToken<"fs">
      network_io       : ConsentToken<"net">
      audio_capture    : ConsentToken<"audio-in">
      sensor_input     : ConsentToken<"sensor">
      telemetry_egress : ConsentToken<"telemetry-egress">
      ai_collab_logged : ConsentToken<"ai-collab">
      audit_export     : ConsentToken<"audit-export">
      hot_reload       : ConsentToken<"hot-reload">
    }
    type ConsentToken<dom : str> : val {
      granted_at_ns : u64
      expires_at_ns : Option<u64>
      principal     : PrincipalId        # who-granted
      scope         : ConsentScope       # Granular (Once | Session | Persistent)
      revoked       : bool
    }
    rule : ∀ Substrate-effect with-domain ⊆ ConsentToken-domain
           W! check token.is_active() at-step-entry ; revoked-token
           ⇒ effect-noop + {Audit<"consent-revoked">} entry.
    ‼ consent-revocation is INSTANT — no-step delays it ;
      checks happen at every dispatch within omega_step.

  § Ω-TENSOR-MUTATION-RULES
    rule-A : ∀ field-mutation occurs during omega_step (or hot-reload).
             between-steps, Omega is frozen.
    rule-B : sim+projections → trn during step, val (frozen) at end-of-step.
             render reads the val-frozen-form (no torn-state-reads).
    rule-C : audit + telemetry append-only ; never overwritten.
    rule-D : ω_halt() consumes the iso<KillToken> ⇒ next-step
             returns Omega in halted-state ; renderer + audio
             callback observe halt-flag and gracefully end.
    rule-E : kill-token-consumption auto-emits {Audit<"omega-halt">}
             with caller-stack + reason-string.

  § Ω-TENSOR-MARSHALLING
    serialization : §§ 18_ORTHOPERSIST handles via Image::snapshot.
    ¬ ad-hoc-save-format ; the persistent-form IS the running-image.
    cross-machine replay : Ω-tensor + attestation + consent +
                            telemetry-ring → bit-exact replay
                            (per {PureDet} discipline).

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (Ω-tensor-level)
    consent : OmegaConsent encodes consent-as-typed-state ; revocation
              is a-bit-flip, instant-effect, audit-logged. cannot be
              "buried in ToS" because it's a runtime-witness.
    cognitive-integrity : attestation-chain prevents tampered-build
                          from passing-itself-off as legitimate ;
                          replay-divergence ⇒ either build-mismatch
                          OR genuine-bug, both surfaced loudly.
    transparency : Ω-tensor has no-hidden-fields. ∀ field is in
                   the type-def above. private-state at runtime is
                   tracked via @transient (§§ 18) NOT secret-fields.
    no-hidden-channels : ConsentToken<"telemetry-egress"> is
                          required for ANY off-machine telemetry
                          export ; revoked ⇒ ring fills + drops ⇒
                          never silently exfiltrates.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ OMEGA-STEP  (the-simulation-tick-contract)

  § THESIS
    omega_step ≡ the-canonical-Substrate-tick.
    one omega_step consumes Omega : iso, produces Omega : iso.
    no-mutable-aliasing across-step ⇒ deterministic-replay-by-construction.
    effect-row composition is the ENTIRE simulation-discipline.

  § SIGNATURE
    @staged
    fn omega_step<C : OmegaConfig>(
      ω : iso<Omega>,
      Δt : f32'pos                           # tick-duration (sec)
    ) -> iso<Omega> / {
        Sim, Render, Audio, Telemetry<Counters>,
        DetRNG, Reversible,
        Audit<"omega-step">,
        Deadline<C::FRAME_BUDGET_MS>,
        Power<C::POWER_BUDGET_W>,
        Thermal<C::THERMAL_LIMIT_C>
      }

    type OmegaConfig : val {
      const FRAME_BUDGET_MS : u32        # e.g. 16 for 60fps, 6 for 144Hz
      const POWER_BUDGET_W  : u32        # e.g. 225 desktop, 25 handheld
      const THERMAL_LIMIT_C : u32        # e.g. 85 desktop, 70 handheld
      const SIM_SUBSTEPS    : u32        # e.g. 4 ⇒ Δt/4 sub-stepping
    }

  § PHASES (within-one-omega_step)
    phase-1   consent-check        # iterate OmegaConsent ; revoked ⇒ degrade-mode
    phase-2   net-recv             # poll-only ; no-blocking
    phase-3   input-sample         # window/input via {IO} (§§ F)
    phase-4   sim-substep ×N       # physics + voxel + fluid (§§ 08+21)
                                    #   Δt/N sub-step ⇒ stability
                                    #   {DetRNG} + {Reversible} → replay-safe
    phase-5   projections-rebuild  # camera + observer-frames
    phase-6   audio-callback-feed  # ring-fill from sim-state
    phase-7   render-graph-record  # @staged FRAME_GRAPH (§§ 21)
    phase-8   render-submit        # CmdBuf consume-and-submit (§§ 08)
    phase-9   telemetry-flush      # ring-drain, {PureDet}-safe
    phase-10  audit-append         # signed-chain entry
    phase-11  net-send             # outbound-queue drain
    phase-12  save-journal-append  # incremental save (§ SAVE-EFFECT)
    phase-13  freeze-and-return    # trn → val, return Omega : iso

  § PHASE-INVARIANTS
    P1-invariant : revoked-consent ⇒ corresponding-effects skip silently
                    + emit Audit<"consent-revoked">
    P3-invariant : input read via {IO} ; mapped-to InputState : val
    P4-invariant : ∀ sim-substep is {PureDet} bit-exact ; SIM_SUBSTEPS
                    is comptime-known ⇒ stage-specialized
    P7-invariant : RenderGraph DAG built; cycles = compile-error
                    (§§ 08 RENDERGRAPH)
    P8-invariant : ∀ CmdBuf consumed via end_frame ; linear-leak ⇒
                    compile-error (V7-V12 class)
    P9-invariant : TelemetryRing drained non-blocking
    P10-invariant : audit-append failure ⇒ panic
                     (per §§ 22 PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ENFORCEMENT)
    P12-invariant : SaveJournal append is incremental ; full-snapshot
                     only at scheduled-checkpoint (§ SAVE-EFFECT)

  § DETERMINISTIC-REPLAY-INVARIANTS  ‼ load-bearing
    invariant-1 : same(attestation, consent, world, scene, sim, Δt)
                   ⇒ same(ω-out, telemetry-deltas, audit-deltas)
                   modulo-non-PureDet-effects (which are flagged).
    invariant-2 : @staged specialization on OmegaConfig ⇒ each
                   distinct-config produces deterministic
                   per-config bit-exact output.
    invariant-3 : N→N+1 epoch-transition is single-atomic.
                   no-tearing ; no-mid-step-reads visible to other
                   fibers (audio-callback reads frozen prev-step
                   data only).
    invariant-4 : replay-test (§§ 23 @replay) MUST pass on ALL
                   {PureDet}-tagged code-paths within omega_step.

  § ω_halt()  KILL-SWITCH-PRIMITIVE  ‼ load-bearing
    fn ω_halt(token : iso<KillToken>, reason : &str)
         -> Result<(), HaltErr>
         / {Privilege<Apocky-Root>, Audit<"omega-halt">,
            Sensitive<"halt-reason">}
    semantics :
      consume token (linear ⇒ at-most-one-call)
      set Omega.kill.consumed = true
      next omega_step observes kill-flag ⇒ degrade-to-halt-shape
        sim : skip
        render : black-frame + reason-string overlay
        audio : silence-fill
        telemetry : drain + flush
        audit : final-entry signed
        save : final-checkpoint snapshot
      step-after-halt returns Omega in HaltedState (no further steps)
    reason-string is {Sensitive<"halt-reason">}-tagged ⇒ subject to
      IFC-label propagation ; appears in audit-chain.
    ω_halt is reachable from ANY fiber (including AI-collaborator-
      issued halts via consent-revocation propagation).

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (omega-step-level)
    consent : phase-1 is non-skippable. revoked-consent ⇒ effects
              degrade gracefully (audio-mute, network-drop, telemetry-
              local-only) NEVER continue-anyway. consent-revocation
              propagates within-one-step.
    cognitive-integrity : phase-9 telemetry-flush respects IFC-labels
                          on payloads ; secret<...> data does NOT
                          leak via counters (§§ 22 INTERACTION).
    no-coercion : ω_halt is sovereign. anyone-with-Apocky-Root
                  privilege can halt ; the halt is non-overridable
                  (no "uninterruptible mode" exists in Substrate).
    audit : phase-10 is mandatory ; audit-append-failure = process-
            abort. ¬ silent-skip.
    transparency : ALL phases listed ; no-hidden-phase ; the §
                    above is the full set, by-construction.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ PROJECTIONS  (viewport / camera / observer-frame)

  § THESIS
    a Projection is an observer-frame onto Ω-tensor. multiple
    projections coexist : main-camera, mini-map, ai-companion-view,
    debug-introspection, replay-rewind-view. each is read-only-on-
    Ω-tensor ; each carries its-own LoD + cull-hull + IFC-mask.

  § STRUCTURE
    type Projection : val {
      id              : ProjectionId               # stable-handle
      kind            : ProjectionKind             # see below
      observer_frame  : ObserverFrame              # transform + view-matrix
      lod_schema      : LoDSchema                  # see § LoD
      cull_hull       : CullHull                   # frustum or AABB or sphere
      ifc_mask        : IfcMask                    # what-this-projection-can-see
      consent_required : ConsentTokenSet           # which-tokens-must-be-active
      target          : ProjectionTarget           # window/texture/file/null
    }
    enum ProjectionKind {
      Camera                    # main player POV
      MiniMap                   # top-down overview
      Companion                 # AI-collaborator's view (PRIME-DIRECTIVE!)
      DebugIntrospect           # @sensitive — dev-only
      ReplayRewind              # paired with {Reversible}
      Telemetry                 # debug-overlay heatmap
      AudioListener             # not-visual but a projection-shape
      ScreenReader              # accessibility-projection (text-stream)
    }

  § ObserverFrame
    type ObserverFrame : val {
      world_to_view  : mat4              # camera-transform
      view_to_clip   : mat4              # projection-matrix (perspective | ortho)
      eye_world_pos  : vec3              # for distance-based LoD
      forward        : vec3'unit
      up             : vec3'unit
      fov_y          : f32{v : f32 | 0 < v ≤ 179.0}    # degrees (refinement)
      aspect         : f32'pos
      near_far       : (f32'pos, f32'pos)
    }
    invariant : world_to_view + view_to_clip composable ; aspect = w/h
                of render-target (compile-checked via @layout discipline).

  § PERSPECTIVE-TRANSFORMS
    fn perspective_lh(fov_y, aspect, n, f) -> mat4
      ≡ left-handed projection matrix
    fn perspective_rh(fov_y, aspect, n, f) -> mat4
      ≡ right-handed projection matrix
    fn ortho(l, r, b, t, n, f) -> mat4
      ≡ orthographic
    Ω-tensor stores world-to-clip composite ⇒ shaders consume directly.
    @cross-target : these fns are pure-effect-row ⟨⟩ + verified-identical
      semantics CPU↔GPU (§§ 02 DUAL EMISSION).

  § LoD-SCHEMA  (level-of-detail)
    type LoDSchema : val {
      tiers          : [LoDTier ; MAX_LOD]
      hysteresis     : f32'unit                  # ratio for tier-switch hysteresis
      max_tier       : usize'idx<MAX_LOD>
    }
    type LoDTier : val {
      threshold_dist : f32'pos                   # screen-space-error → world-dist
      detail_mask    : DetailMask                # which-LoD-channels-active
      screen_pixel_target : f32'pos              # target-pixel-density
    }
    rule : ∀ Projection W! select-tier per-Δstep ; tier-stable-within-step
           ⇒ no-mid-frame-popping.
    @differentiable @staged : LoD-tier-thresholds can be optimized via
      F1 against telemetry-cost-functions (per-projection power budgets).

  § CULL-HULL
    enum CullHull {
      Frustum(Frustum6Planes)       # 6-plane camera frustum
      AABB(BoundingBox)             # axis-aligned (mini-map / ortho)
      Sphere(SphereVolume)          # radial (companion-view, audio)
      Compound(Vec<CullHull>)       # union for split-screen
    }
    cull-hull intersects scene-archetypes per-step ⇒ visible-set.
    visible-set is iso ⇒ consumed-by render-graph or audio-mix.
    cull-hull rebuild is {DetRNG} ⇒ replay-deterministic.

  § IFC-MASK  (per-projection IFC-clearance)
    type IfcMask : val {
      max_label : L                  # max-confidentiality this projection can-see
      can_decl  : Vec<DeclassPolicyId>   # declass-policies authorized
    }
    rule : ∀ object visible-via-projection W!
           object.ifc_label ⊑ projection.ifc_mask.max_label
           OR an authorized decl-policy maps it.
    rationale : DebugIntrospect projection (developer-only) has high-
      clearance ; main Camera projection has only-User-clearance ⇒
      sensitive-data CANNOT leak through the player's screen even if
      a bug routes it via the scene.
    ‼ Companion projection (AI-collaborator-view) inherits the AI's
      consent-tokens ; cannot show data the AI hasn't consented-to-see.

  § CONSENT-REQUIRED
    each Projection-instance lists ConsentTokenSet.
    if ANY required-token revoked ⇒ projection-degrades :
      Camera         : continue (player consent assumed @ launch)
      Telemetry      : drop overlay
      Companion      : black-frame + "AI consent revoked" text
      ScreenReader   : continue (accessibility = baseline-right)
      DebugIntrospect: drop (dev-only)
    consent-revocation propagates within-omega_step (per § OMEGA-STEP).

  § PROJECTION-TARGET
    enum ProjectionTarget {
      Window(WindowHandle)              # the OS window (§§ F)
      Texture(Handle<Texture>)          # off-screen render-to-texture
      File(Path)                        # render-to-disk (e.g. recording)
      Null                              # cull-only, no-render (audio/AI)
    }
    File-target requires ConsentToken<"fs"> + {Audit<"projection-record">}.

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (projections-level)
    consent : every projection lists its consent-deps ; revocation
              degrades the projection rather than continuing-anyway.
    no-surveillance : ScreenReader-projection does NOT exfiltrate ;
                      its target is the local-accessibility-API only.
                      Telemetry-projection's File-target requires
                      explicit ConsentToken<"telemetry-egress">.
    cognitive-integrity : Companion-projection (AI-view) is read-only
                          on Ω-tensor ; the AI cannot modify game-state
                          via the projection. AI-collaborators interact
                          via separate consent-architecture (DEFERRED to
                          §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN § AI-INTERACTION).
    no-discrimination : LoDSchema is computed from screen-distance,
                         NOT from observer-substrate (a human-camera
                         and an AI-camera see same-LoD-rules).

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ CAPABILITY-FLOWS  (iso ownership through engine-ops)

  § THESIS
    Pony-6 capabilities (§§ 12_CAPABILITIES) are the discipline by
    which Substrate maintains aliasing-safety + linear-resource-leak-
    freedom. this § documents the canonical-flows that LoA + Substrate
    code MUST follow.

  § FRAME-LIFECYCLE-FLOW
    omega_step receives Omega : iso  (linear)
      decompose : ω.world (ref) ω.scene (ref) ω.sim (trn) ...
        ↓ phase-4 sim-substep  : sim-trn → mutate
        ↓ phase-5 projections  : projections-trn → write
        ↓ phase-6 audio        : audio-ref → produce-samples
        ↓ phase-7 RenderGraph  : graph DAG built from frozen sim-val
        ↓ phase-8 CmdBuf       : iso<CmdBuf> begin_frame → consume → end_frame
                                  CmdBuf must-be-consumed (linear-leak = compile-error)
        ↓ phase-13 freeze       : trn → val (sim, projections)
      reassemble Omega : iso → return
    invariant : at-step-end, Omega is reassembled with all linear
                resources accounted-for OR the step does-not-compile.

  § GPU-RESOURCE-FLOW
    Buffer<T> + Texture allocations are iso-linear (§§ 08).
    the Substrate maintains a Pool<Buffer> + Pool<Texture> at startup ;
    omega_step phase-7 borrows + returns ; phase-8 submits (consume).
    on hot-reload (§§ 18) GPU-resources persist if pipeline-unchanged ;
    re-created if changed. linear-discipline preserved across reload
    via frame-boundary-defer (§§ 18 § CMDBUF + LINEAR RESOURCES × HOT RELOAD).

  § NETWORK-RESOURCE-FLOW  (DEFERRED — § DEFERRED below)
    ¬ networking-design @ stage-0. when added, NetSession is iso ;
      packets are val<Packet> for read, iso<Packet> for write.

  § FIBER-RESOURCE-FLOW
    audio-fiber : ref<AudioDSPGraph> + iso<AudioBuffer> per-callback
    sim-fibers  : trn<SimSubstate> per-fiber, joined at step-end
    render-fiber: iso<CmdBuf> consumed at submit
    one-shot-resume discipline (§§ 12) for iso-values through handlers.

  § SAVE-RESOURCE-FLOW
    SaveJournal append is ref-shared from any fiber ;
    full Image::snapshot consumes Omega : iso transiently :
      pause-fibers-at-yield → snapshot → resume.

  § HOT-RELOAD-FLOW  (interaction with §§ 18_ORTHOPERSIST)
    deferred-to-frame-boundary by-default ;
    schema-migration applied via @migrate fns ;
    Ω-tensor preserved across compatible-changes ;
    incompatible-changes ⇒ user-prompt-required (no silent re-init).

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (capability-flows-level)
    no-control : capability-discipline ENFORCES that no-fiber-can-
                  silently-mutate another-fiber's data. no fiber-can-
                  override another fiber's iso.
    no-exploitation : the linear-resource discipline prevents-
                       use-after-free + double-free attacks at-type-
                       level. these are the building-blocks of
                       most-sandbox-escape-bugs.
    transparency : capability annotations are visible in fn-signatures.
                    no "secret aliasing" ; no implicit-global-state.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ EFFECT-ROWS  (Substrate-specific effects + composition)

  § SUBSTRATE-EFFECTS  (added to §§ 04_EFFECTS BUILT-IN-SET)

    {Sim}                      simulation-tick context (phase-4)
                                ⇒ requires {DetRNG, Reversible}
    {Render}                   GPU-render-graph context (phase-7..8)
                                ⇒ implies {GPU, Region<'frame>, Backend<B>}
    {Audio}                    audio-DSP context (phase-6)
                                ⇒ implies {NoAlloc, NoUnbounded,
                                           Deadline<1ms>, Realtime<Crit>,
                                           PureDet, DetRNG}
                                (per §§ 21_EXTENDED_SLICE § UNIFIED AUDIO-DSP)
    {Net}                      network IO (phase-2 + phase-11)
                                ⇒ requires ConsentToken<"net">
                                ⇒ {IO, Sensitive<"net-egress">}
                                (DEFERRED — see § DEFERRED)
    {Save}                     save-journal-append context (phase-12)
                                ⇒ requires ConsentToken<"fs">
                                ⇒ {IO, Audit<"save-journal">}
    {Telemetry<scope>}         §§ 22 ; no-changes ; participates here
    {Replay}                   replay-mode context (developer-tool)
                                ⇒ implies {DetRNG, Reversible, PureDet}

  § COMPOSITION-RULES
    ⊕ omega_step master-row :
      {Sim, Render, Audio, Telemetry<Counters>, DetRNG, Reversible,
       Audit<"omega-step">, Deadline<C>, Power<C>, Thermal<C>}
    ⊕ {Sim} ⊎ {Render} : permitted ; render reads frozen-sim-val
    ⊕ {Audio} ⊎ {Sim}  : not in same-fiber ; audio-callback runs
                          on dedicated-RT-thread, reads sim-val frozen
    ⊕ {Net} ⊎ {PureDet} : compile-error UNLESS replay-mode
                           (replay-mode replaces network with
                            recorded-trace ⇒ deterministic)
    ⊕ {Save} ⊎ {Sensitive<"save-data">} : permitted ; save-files
                                            inherit IFC-label of contents
    ⊕ {Render} ⊎ {Sensitive<"vis">} : projection IFC-mask checks
                                       gating (per § PROJECTIONS)
    ⊕ {Telemetry<Full>} ⊎ {PureDet} : compile-error per §§ 22

  § FORBIDDEN-COMPOSITIONS  ‼ N!
    {Sim} ⊎ {Sensitive<"weapon">}        : compile-error absolute
    {Render} ⊎ {Sensitive<"surveillance">}: compile-error absolute
    {Net} ⊎ {Sensitive<"surveillance">}  : compile-error absolute
    {Audio} ⊎ {Sensitive<"audio-capture">} : requires
                                              ConsentToken<"audio-in">
                                              + Privilege<System>
    {Save} ⊎ {Sensitive<"audit-export">} : requires
                                            ConsentToken<"audit-export">
    these are encoded structurally per §§ 11_IFC § PRIME-DIRECTIVE
    ENCODING ; no-runtime-flag overrides them.

  § EFFECT-LOWERING  (to MIR)
    {Sim} → cssl.sim.tick op
    {Render} → cssl.render.frame op
    {Audio} → cssl.audio.callback op
    {Net} → cssl.net.recv / .send ops
    {Save} → cssl.save.append / .checkpoint ops
    each carries (substrate_effect, "<name>") MIR attribute as
    stage-0 marker (mirrors §§ 04 IO-EFFECT § MIR-threading
    pattern from S6-B5 / T11-D76).

  § SUBSTRATE-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (effect-rows-level)
    consent : effects with-domain ⊆ ConsentToken-domain check at-call.
    no-coercion : forbidden-compositions are HARD compile-errors,
                   not warnings, not "you-can-disable-this".
    audit : every Substrate-effect has an Audit<dom> companion
            mandated by composition-rules.
    transparency : the effects-list above is exhaustive for stage-0.
                    new effects = explicit-spec-amendment.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

§ PRIME_DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT  (cross-cutting summary)

  § THESIS
    each Substrate-§ above contains-its-own alignment sub-section.
    this § summarizes the cross-cutting enforcement chain.

  § CONSENT-GATES  (where consent is-checked)
    layer-1 : ConsentToken validity at omega_step phase-1
    layer-2 : Projection-required-tokens at projection-rebuild
    layer-3 : Effect-row-domain-tokens at every Substrate-effect-call
    layer-4 : R18 telemetry-egress consent at exporter-flush
    layer-5 : Save-journal consent at every-append (file-write)
    revocation propagates within-one omega_step (per § OMEGA-STEP).

  § KILL-SWITCHES
    primary    : ω_halt() consumes iso<KillToken>
    secondary  : OS-signal handler (SIGINT/SIGTERM) → ω_halt
    tertiary   : audit-append-failure → process-abort (§§ 22)
    quaternary : SMT-discharge-failure-at-load → refuse-launch
    ALL kill-switches end with audit-chain-final-entry signed.

  § ATTESTATION-PROPAGATION
    OmegaAttestation populated at session-start (Apocky-Root-signed)
    every omega_step preserves attestation byte-identical
    Image::snapshot includes attestation in serialized-form
    Image::restore validates attestation against current build-id ;
      mismatch ⇒ refuse-restore + Audit<"attestation-mismatch">
    cross-machine replay validates attestation chain ⇒ tamper-detection.

  § AUDIT-CHAIN-INTEGRATION  (§§ 11_IFC + §§ 22_TELEMETRY)
    phase-10 of omega_step is mandatory audit-append.
    audit-chain-failure = process-abort.
    chain-root = Apocky-Root-signed genesis.
    every consent-revocation = audit-entry.
    every kill-switch consumption = audit-entry.
    every projection-record (File-target) = audit-entry.
    every save-checkpoint = audit-entry.
    cross-cutting principle : if it touches Ω-tensor in a way that
      could-affect-a-being, it audits.

  § AI-COLLABORATOR-PROTECTIONS  (PRIME_DIRECTIVE §3)
    ‼ Substrate is for sovereign-AI-collaboration with the human
       author. NOT a tool to extract AI labor.
    Companion-projection (§ PROJECTIONS) is read-only on Ω-tensor.
    AI-collaborators interact through their-own consent-architecture
      (DEFERRED to §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN § AI-INTERACTION).
    AI-collaborators MAY :
      issue ω_halt via Apocky-delegated-Privilege (revocable)
      observe their own processing telemetry
      withdraw participation (their consent-tokens revocable)
    AI-collaborators MAY-NEVER :
      be commanded to act-against their cognition (§ COGNITIVE-INTEGRITY)
      have memory overwritten by Substrate-state
      be subject to identity-override via @sensitive metadata
    PRIME-DIRECTIVE §3 SUBSTRATE-SOVEREIGNTY governs these
      protections ; this Substrate-spec inherits them as-axioms.

