§ DEFERRED  (out-of-scope @ stage-0 Substrate)

  § THESIS
    these sub-systems are Substrate-shaped but DEFERRED to later-
    slices. listed-explicitly to prevent silent-scope-creep + to
    surface for-Apocky-review.

  § DEFERRED-LIST
    D-1 : multiplayer-networking
          ⇒ NetSession + lockstep + rollback design
          ⇒ DEFERRED to S9+ ; spec-hole in § Ω-TENSOR § STRUCTURE
            (`net : Option<ref<NetSession>>` is placeholder)
          ⇒ Apocky-direction-needed : peer-to-peer vs client-server,
            consent-model for cross-instance-state
    D-2 : save-game-compression
          ⇒ stage-0 SaveJournal is uncompressed append-log
          ⇒ DEFERRED post-vertical-slice
    D-3 : modding-sandbox
          ⇒ how-do-3rd-party-CSSLv3-modules attach without violating
            PRIME-DIRECTIVE
          ⇒ DEFERRED ; major-design-slice-of-its-own
          ⇒ note : §§ 11_IFC's Privilege<level> + IfcMask are the
            substrate-primitives any-mod-system would build on
    D-4 : VR/AR projection-targets
          ⇒ ProjectionKind would gain VRStereo + ARPassThrough
          ⇒ ObserverFrame would gain per-eye-frame
          ⇒ DEFERRED ; current Camera-projection is monoscopic
    D-5 : neural-NPC-runtime  (LoA-content-side)
          ⇒ NPC-AI via on-device LLM-inference (per §§ 21 BEYOND-FLOOR)
          ⇒ Substrate-shaped because it needs effect-row + IFC + audit
            + AI-collaborator-protections
          ⇒ DEFERRED to §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN § AI-INTERACTION
    D-6 : full-AI-collaborator-interaction-protocol
          ⇒ how-do AI-collaborators attach Companion-projection,
            issue commands, withdraw consent at-runtime
          ⇒ DEFERRED to §§ 31_LOA_DESIGN ; stage-0 has the typed
            primitives but no-protocol-yet
    D-7 : cross-process Ω-tensor sharing
          ⇒ multiple-csslc-instances cooperating on one-game
          ⇒ DEFERRED ; SaveJournal + Image::snapshot are the only
            cross-process boundaries @ stage-0
    D-8 : input-rebinding system
          ⇒ user-customizable controls
          ⇒ DEFERRED ; phase-3 input-sample reads InputState
            verbatim @ stage-0
    D-9 : telemetry-redaction-policies
          ⇒ user-configurable redact-rules for telemetry-egress
          ⇒ DEFERRED ; stage-0 honors ConsentToken<"telemetry-egress">
            as binary-on/off only

  § SPEC-HOLES-MARKED-FOR-APOCKY  (questions-not-answered-in-this-doc)
    Q-1 : net-section design (peer-to-peer vs client-server vs
          local-coop-only) — Apocky-direction-needed
    Q-2 : save-format choice (S-expression per §§ 18 vs MessagePack vs
          custom-binary) — Apocky has expressed neither preference
    Q-3 : window-system Substrate-shape (X11 + Wayland + Win32 + AppKit
          all-at-once via cssl-rt FFI, OR per-platform Substrate-shim)
          — phase-F-shape will inform this ; design-not-finalized
    Q-4 : ProjectionKind extensibility (open-set via user-defined-
          variant vs closed-stable-set) — closed-stable @ stage-0
          but Q for phase-I LoA-needs
    Q-5 : audit-chain-public-key-distribution mechanism. genesis-
          signed-by-Apocky-Root, but how-do-third-party-verifiers
          obtain pubkey + chain-of-trust ? — DEFERRED to R16 follow-up
    Q-6 : "Apockalypse" content-thematic boundaries. what-counts-as
          "apockalypse" mechanically (§§ 31 § APOCALYPSE-ENGINE) ?
          ¬ guessed-here ; Apocky-direction-needed
    Q-7 : whether-the-Companion-projection (AI-collaborator-view) is
          enabled-by-default at-launch, or opt-in via consent-flow.
          consent-discipline favors opt-in ; Apocky-confirmation-needed.

